  "texts": [
    "This Section provides a conceptual framework to categorize new technologies used in migration and asylum decisionmaking in Europe.",
    "In addition to solely automated decisions, I have illustrated three further categories of ADM: automated triage, suspicion, and evidence.",
    "These categories focus on the outputs of the automated system; they do not define the overall decision-making process and are not isolated in watertight compartments.",
    "In some cases, the same system performs more than one role in the decision-making processes.",
    "Regarding visas, automated systems classify the application, make positive decisions if no issue arises, or flag it to a human case worker when assessed as suspicious."
  ],
